            <img src="images/value_education-dollars3a.jpg" />
            <p> There are many reasons to become skilled with reading, writing,
            computers, and mathematics. A big one is the monetary value
            employers place on literate employees. The weekly take-home paycheck
            of an employee with a college degree is over 2.25 times that of a
            person without a high school degree. Persons without a high school
            degree are almost 3 times more likely to be unemployed than those
            with a college degree. Learn more facts about literacy in the U.S.
            and elsewhere at our <a href="resources.html#literacy">internet resources page.</a>
            </p>

        </div> <!-- class=grid_4 -->
        
